hon, J.J., Ayress, M.A., De Deckker, P., Microfossil and stable-isotope evidence for changes in Late Holocene palaeoproductivity and palaeoceanographic conditions in the Prydz Bay region of Antarctica (1997) Palaeogeography, Palaeoclimatology, Palaeoecology, 131 (3-4), pp. 485-510; Renssen, H., Goosse, H., Fichefet, T., Massom-Delmotte, V., Koç, N., Holocene climate evolution in the high-latitude Southern Hemisphere simulated by a coupled atmosphere-sea-ice-ocean-vegetation model (2005) The Holocene, 15 (7), pp. 951-964; Renssen, H., Seppä, H., Heiri, O., Roche, D.M., Goosse, H., Fichefet, T., The spatial and temporal complexity of the Holocene thermal maximum (2009) Nature Geoscience, 2 (6), pp. 411-414; Shemesh, A., Hodell, D., Crosta, X., Kanfoush, S., Charles, C., Guilderson, T., Sequence of events during the last deglaciation in Southern Ocean sediments and Antarctic ice cores (2002) Paleoceanography, 17 (4), p. 1056; Sinninghe Damste, J.S., Rijpstra, W.I.C., Schouten, S., Fuerst, J.A., Jetten, M.S.M., Strous, M., The occurrence of hopanoids in planctomycetes: implications for the sedimentary biomarker record (2004) Organic Geochemistry, 35 (5), pp. 561-566; Smith, N., Tréguer, P., (1994) Physical and chemical oceanography in the vicinity of Prydz bay, Antarctica. In ""Southern Ocean Ecology: The BIOMASS Perspective"", , Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, 25-45; Smith, N.R., Zhaoquian, D., Kerry, K.R., Wright, S., Water masses and circulation in the of Prydz Bay, Antarctica (1984) Deep-Sea Research I, 31 (9), pp. 1121-1147; Stammerjohn, S.E., Martinson, D.G., Smith, R.C., Yuan, X., Rind, D., Trends in Antarctic annual sea ice retreat and advance and their relation to El Niño-Southern Oscillation and Southern Annular Mode variability (2008) Journal of Geophysical Research C: Oceans, 113 (3); Stenni, B., Masson-Delmotte, V., Johnsen, S., Jouzel, J., Longinelli, A., Monnin, E., Rothlisberger, R., Selmo, E., An oceanic cold reversal during the last deglaciation